Subagent/Workflow-agent prompts must delegate, never restate: dispatching gm-driven work via Agent() or Workflow agent()/pipeline() should say only 'use the gm skill for this' plus task-specific content (target, investigation scope, report shape) -- never inline verb names, spool file paths, JSON body shapes, or phase-chain mechanics into the prompt string. Skill(skill='gm') already supplies all protocol detail on invocation; restating it in a prompt is instructional content living outside plugkit+skill, the exact anti-pattern gm's architecture exists to prevent. Caught when a prior session wrote long full-protocol-explanation prompts for 6 parallel sibling-repo survey subagents instead of minimal pointers.